ns:item.ns:title: U.S. Geological Survey, 2006, FGDC Digital Cartographic Standard for Geologic Map Symbolization (PostScript Implementation): U.S. Geological Survey Techniques and Methods 11-A2
FGDC Geologic Patterns for the Web

rdf:Description.dc:description: Converted from 'FGDC Geologic Patterns for the Web' to QGIS compatible svg symbols, with customisable fill colour/stroke colour/stroke width (when appropriate). SVG scaled to 50x50 pixels so that base outline-width is 0.387 px and width is 90 in the QGIS xml definition file. Some of the original FGDC symbols have been omitted from this set because they can be generated from other symbols using the 'texture width' and/or 'stroke width' fields in QGIS symbology form.
rdf:Description.dc:creator: GeoProc.com
